Description: Fragment of flattened handle with a gradual curve from a pottery transport amphora. Clay fine orange-pink; cream slip. Circular stamp at top of handle with Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Name Armosilas. Trimmed. Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p.71, 15. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0925.12.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0691)
